If you are looking for amenities and luxury and to be catered to then perhaps you should keep looking.	If you are used to the large North American style hotels and amenities without the old world character, than this is not the place for you but of course you are going to have to pay a substantial premium to get that kind of service.	I would definitely recommend it to travelers to Rome looking for a nice, but not luxury spot.	In summary if you are not looking for great American style luxury and would like to be at the center of all Roman sites and nightlife Hotel Navona is a great affordable option.